<DESCRIPT>  MIDEAST; MILITARY; PROTEST; LIST  </DESCRIPT>
<LEADPARA>  As troops in the Persian Gulf prepare for battle, Bay Area peace activists are
accelerating their efforts to stop the war before it begins.; Today:  </LEADPARA>
<SECTION>  Local  </SECTION>
<HEADLINE>  PROTESTS FOR PEACE  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>  (box)Santa Cruz: 10 a.m. march beginning on the campus of the University of
California, Santa Cruz, and ending with a noon rally at the city's San Lorenzo
Park.; (box)Mountain View: Peace vigil 1:30 to 3 p.m. on Castro Street at El
Camino Real.; (box)Fremont: Prayer vigil at 6:30 p.m. at the First United
Methodist Church, 2950 Washington Blvd.; (box)San Jose: Peace vigil from 5
p.m. to 7 p.m. at Plaza Park on Market Street downtown.; Monday:; (box)San
Francisco: "Golden Gate Bridge Walk" at 6:30 a.m. beginning at the Marin vista
point. Participants are asked to bring a "body bag."; (box)San Jose: "Assembly
of Conscience" at 5:45 p.m. in the plaza at Market and San Carlos streets,
followed by a candlelight march through downtown San Jose. At 7 p.m., there
will be an interfaith peace service at St. Joseph's Cathedral at Market and
San Fernando streets, followed by an 8:30 p.m. procession to the federal
building, 280 S. First St., where an all-night vigil will be held.; (box)Santa
Cruz: "A Call for Peace" at Pacific Cultural Center, Broadway and Seabright
Avenue, from 7 to 10 p.m. An evening to pray, sing and discuss the gulf
crisis.; (box)Santa Clara: Students at Santa Clara University plan to join
hands in a peace demonstration at 10:20 a.m. in front of Mission Church.;
(box)Fremont: Tri-Cities Ministerial Association will gather at noon at
Mission San Jose for a prayer vigil. The mission bell will be rung every 15
minutes until 1 p.m. -- midnight the next day in Baghdad. There will also be a
"speak-out, teach-in" at 7 p.m. at the Fremont Main Library, Paseo Padre
Parkway and Stevenson Boulevard, in the Fuyaya A Room. A Vietnam veteran and a
Palestinian will be the speakers.; (box)Los Altos: Foothill Baptist Church,
1347 Richardson Ave., will open the doors of its sanctuary from 6 a.m. to 10
p.m. for people to pray for a peaceful resolution of Persian Gulf crisis.; 
Tuesday:; (box)San Francisco: Attempted 7 a.m. shutdown of the federal
building at 450 Golden Gate Ave., followed by a march through the Mission
District beginning at 5:30 p.m. at 24th and Mission streets. If a war begins,
the Emergency Committee to Stop the U.S. War in the Middle East has asked
protesters to gather at 5 p.m. that day at Powell and Market streets.;
Saturday:; (box)San Francisco: Protest march at Mission Dolores Park at 11
a.m., concluding with a Civic Center Rally at 1 p.m.; Jan. 26; (box)San
Francisco: March at 10 a.m. at Justin Herman Plaza, ending with a Civic Center
rally.  </TEXT>
